{
  "stem": "27509.4",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And-- and every night we used to give up our beds, the children used to give our beds, to bring people in to give them a night's sleep.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And ultimately we had two families and we give-- to each of them we gave a room of their own.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "One was a rabbi and his wife and daughter, and another one was a family from Lodz, I think, also with a wife and a daughter.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "[NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I remember even the name of the other family.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And so they have taken a permanent stay with us to be fed and housed fully.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And every night and every day it was coming and going all the time.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "People came-- strangers-- and we used to feed them.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "We used to do what we could for them.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "But-- and then there was not enough bread.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Not only was not enough bread in terms of-- of flour, there was not enough facilities in a city of 100,000 people to bake for 300,000 people, in pure technical terms.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "So we used to get up-- I used to get up at 3:00 in the morning-- up at 3:00 in the morning, go to the other end of town where there was the bakery, and stand in a queue, and at 7 o'clock in the morning come home with a whole-- with a loaf of bread-- round, like, loaf of bread.",
      "word_count": 61
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And that was a major achievement, day in and day out, that loaf of bread.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Those were the immediate impacts of-- of that.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And-- and of course, as long as it doesn't touch you, you think that you are charitable and you are in a different category.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "The others were the-- the refugees.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "You were in your own home.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Sure.",
      "word_count": 1
    }
  ],
